description: The Indian rupee hit a record low against the dollar, closing at 84.85. Sanjay Malhotra's appointment as RBI governor sparked speculation of a dovish policy shift, with analysts predicting a rate cut as early as February. This expectation, coupled with India's weak economic outlook, could further depreciate the rupee to 86 by March 2025.
title: Re hits record low on buzz of Malhotra being dovish

description: Sanjay Malhotra, the incoming RBI chief, is expected to focus on growth and technology adoption within the banking sector.  Brokerages are divided on whether he will prioritize faster interest rate easing. While some anticipate a more accommodative monetary policy given his finance background, others believe the chances of a rate cut have diminished.
title: Brokerages are split over new RBI governor's rate move

description: Opposition parties initiated a motion to remove Vice President Jagdeep Dhankhar as Rajya Sabha chairman, citing bias and unfair conduct.  They accused him of favoring the ruling party and denying the opposition opportunities to respond.  Although the initial notice may not meet procedural deadlines, the opposition plans to resubmit it in the next session.
title: TMC first came up with idea of no-trust motion against VP

description: The INDIA opposition bloc has initiated a motion to remove Vice-President Jagdeep Dhankhar from his role as Rajya Sabha chairman, citing partisan conduct. Parliamentary Affairs Minister Kiren Rijiju condemned the move as disrespectful and a diversionary tactic from alleged Congress-Soros links, while defending Dhankhar's impartiality.
title: In a first, opposition submits notice for VP's removal

description: Sugandha Hiremath, sister of Bharat Forge chairman Baba Kalyani, has challenged the validity of her late mother's two wills in a Pune court. She alleges coercion and undue influence by her brothers, Baba and Gaurishankar Kalyani, who are primary beneficiaries. The wills, made in 2012 and 2022, bequeath shares in Kalyani Group companies, properties, and jewelry.
title: Baba Kalyani's sister challenges validity of mom's wills in court

description: Supreme Court is reviewing a controversial speech by Allahabad High Court Judge Shekhar Kumar Yadav, where he allegedly endorsed majoritarian views and made derogatory remarks about a religious minority.  The apex court has requested a report from the High Court amidst calls for the judge's impeachment and concerns about judicial impartiality.
title: HC judge's speech at VHP event stirs row, SC takes note

description: A Bengaluru automobile executive died by suicide amid a contentious divorce and child custody battle.  His brother alleges the deceased's wife and in-laws demanded exorbitant sums for case withdrawal and visitation rights, driving him to the extreme step.  Police have registered an abetment to suicide case based on a suicide note and video detailing the alleged harassment.
title: Techie ends life over 'Rs 3cr demand' by wife, in-laws

description: RJD leader Lalu Prasad Yadav has publicly endorsed Mamata Banerjee to lead the INDIA opposition bloc, echoing similar sentiments from Sharad Pawar.  Congress downplayed the matter, with Rahul Gandhi reportedly dismissing it as media hype.  However, unease simmers among allies over Congress's perceived unilateralism and focus on the Adani issue, while concerns about Congress's electoral performance fuel the leadership debate.
title: After Pawar, Lalu backs Didi to lead INDIA bloc

description: The Chhattisgarh government, after a successful campaign against Maoists, plans to transform Bastar into a tourism hub. Chitrakote Falls is poised to become a major attraction. A rehabilitation policy offers housing, skills training, and stipends to surrendered Maoists and victims of violence, furthering the government's goal of a Maoist-free Bastar.
title: Bastar will soon be known for tourism: Chhattisgarh CM Vishnu Deo Sai
SM Krishna, man who built Brand Bengaluru

description: India is pushing for a per capita subsidy approach in global fishing negotiations.  The current aggregate model favors wealthy nations with large fishing industries, disadvantaging countries like India that provide smaller individual subsidies to support livelihoods.
title: At WTO, India cites fishing subsidy gap, seeks relook

description: Congress's data analytics head, Praveen Chakravarty, has written to the Chief Election Commissioner, urging for the public release of Maharashtra's assembly-wise voter rolls for the 2024 Lok Sabha and state polls.
title: Make public poll rolls, booth-wise turnout in Maha, Congress tells EC

description: Sebi plans to leverage the government's DigiLocker system to address unclaimed assets in the securities market.  By integrating demat and mutual fund holding statements, and information on investor deaths, Sebi aims to streamline the transfer of assets to rightful heirs.  This initiative will consolidate individuals' financial holdings within their DigiLocker accounts and notify nominees upon the account holder's demise.
title: Sebi taps DigiLocker to ease unclaimed assets transfer

description: Amazon India's senior VP, Amit Agarwal, amidst regulatory scrutiny, affirms compliance and advocates for progressive e-commerce policies.  He emphasizes investments in logistics and infrastructure, not cash burn, and highlights a new quick commerce pilot program in Bangalore. Agarwal reiterates Amazon's long-term commitment to India's growth.
title: Hope for progressive regulatory regime: Amazon

description: RBI Governor Shaktikanta Das, in his final press conference, emphasized the crucial coordination between the RBI and the government in managing inflation. He defended the RBI's stance on maintaining stable rates despite slowing growth, highlighting the impact of multiple factors.
title: Balancing inflation, growth key task for governor: Shaktikanta Das
Mother sells newborn to settle debts in Karnataka, arrested

description: An Intelligence Bureau officer caused a bomb scare on a Nagpur-Kolkata flight, forcing an emergency landing in Raipur.  The officer, Animesh Mandal, claimed a 'personal asset' informed him about the bomb.  A search revealed nothing. Mandal was arrested and refused bail, stating he'd only reveal his source to Modi or Trump.
title: Man held for bomb scare is an IB officer

description: Mediapart, a French investigative outlet, has accused India's ruling BJP of twisting its report on OCCRP funding to allege a US plot against the Indian government. Mediapart's director condemned the BJP's actions as politically motivated and an attack on press freedom, clarifying their report offered no support for such claims.
title: French outlet slams BJP, says its report used for political gain

description: Prime Minister Narendra Modi paid tribute to the martyrs of the Assam Movement on Swahid Diwas, praising their courage and sacrifices. He emphasized their role in preserving Assam's culture and identity, linking it to the state's development.  The BJP aims to connect with the movement's legacy to strengthen its political position in Assam.
title: 'Their valour inspires us': PM Modi hails Assam Movement martyrs

description: Parliamentary proceedings were disrupted on Tuesday as BJP and Congress clashed over the Adani controversy and alleged Congress links with George Soros.  Lok Sabha Speaker urged members to maintain decorum.  Rajya Sabha witnessed noisy scenes as Congress demanded a debate on the Adani issue, leading to adjournment.  The Leader of the House questioned Congress's alleged association with Soros-funded organizations.
title: Logjam in both Houses again as BJP, Congress spar over Adani, Soros

description: Home Minister Amit Shah is pushing for full implementation of the new criminal laws in Haryana by March 31, 2025.  He chaired a review meeting, emphasizing the use of technology for scientific evidence and higher conviction rates.  Shah set a deadline and instructed officials to monitor progress, ensuring timely justice and adherence to timelines for case investigations.
title: Ensure 100% implementation of new criminal laws in Haryana, says Shah

description: RSS functionary Sunil Ambekar urged for exploring alternative solutions if talks with Bangladesh fail to protect Hindus.  Ambekar, speaking at a rally, referenced recent talks between India and Bangladesh, expressing hope for a resolution through dialogue. He emphasized India's support for minorities facing atrocities in neighboring countries, asserting that India must take action if external interventions prove ineffective.
title: If talks fail, explore 'other options' to save Bangladesh Hindus: RSS neta

description: A protest by the Lingayat Panchamasali community in Belagavi, India, demanding increased reservation quotas, turned violent.  Police clashed with protesters who attempted to breach barricades, resulting in injuries and arrests.  Internal disputes within the BJP surfaced during the demonstration, adding to the chaotic scene.
title: Lingayat quota stir turns violent in Karnataka, 50 hurt

description: Congress questioned the BJP government's inaction against George Soros if he is truly involved in anti-India activities. They highlighted India's contributions to a UN fund that supports Soros's foundation and pointed to a PMO advisor's past grant from Soros's organization.
title: Soros-stung Congress hits back, links bizman to PM's adviser

description: President Murmu addressed the National Human Rights Commission on Human Rights Day, highlighting AI's growing influence and potential misuse.  She emphasized emerging human rights threats like cybercrimes and climate change in the digital age, urging stakeholders to address these challenges and protect individual rights.  She also called for safeguarding gig workers' mental health amidst evolving economic models.
title: AI can be misused, climate change a new threat to rights: President Murmu

description: In Dehri, Jaunpur, around 60-70 Muslims have adopted Hindu surnames, claiming Hindu ancestry while continuing to practice Islam.  They believe this bridges the communal divide, citing historical family ties and the use of similar titles in other communities without controversy.  While some have traced their lineage back to Brahmin roots, they maintain they have no intention of converting to Hinduism.
title: Return to roots? Village where Naushad calls himself Dubey & Irshad is Pandey

description: The Supreme Court is examining whether a spouse can back out of a divorce settlement after agreeing to it in court. A husband challenged a Bombay High Court ruling that allowed his wife to retract her consent, despite a signed financial agreement and joint statement.
title: SC to study if spouse can renege after consenting to divorce, financial deal
Chhattisgarh IPS man set to get back job as SC terms ouster vendetta

description: The Supreme Court voiced concerns over the increasing misuse of dowry harassment laws by women against in-laws. The court stressed that vague complaints lacking specific allegations should be dismissed early, preventing the law's use for vindictive purposes.
title: Stop anti-dowry law's misuse to harass innocent in-laws: SC

description: Breaking barriers in a traditionally male-dominated industry, Singareni Collieries Company Limited (SCCL) is set to allocate two coal mines, one underground and one open-cast, exclusively for women workers in Telangana's Godavarikhani coal belt. Starting January 2025, the open-cast mine will be operational, followed by the underground mine in March or April.
title: Singareni to reserve 2 of its coal mines for women staff

description: Seventy-five Indian nationals, including 44 pilgrims from Jammu and Kashmir, were evacuated from Syria to Lebanon due to escalating security concerns.  The Indian government, coordinating through its embassies in Damascus and Beirut, facilitated their safe passage.  Remaining Indians in Syria are urged to contact the embassy for assistance.
title: 75 Indians evacuated from Syria: MEA

description: The CBI awaits sanction from the West Bengal government to prosecute two former R G Kar Medical College & Hospital officials in a financial irregularities case linked to the August rape-murder of a doctor.  The chargesheet was filed on November 29, two days after the sanction request.  Meanwhile, the trial against the main accused in the rape-murder is nearing completion.
title: SC to WB: Expedite nod for prosecution of RGK ex-principal

description: The Supreme Court prioritized estranged wives and children's maintenance over creditors' claims in insolvency cases.  Justices ruled that maintenance, tied to the right to dignity, overrides claims under the Insolvency and Bankruptcy Code.  The court upheld its interim order, setting maintenance lower than the high court's initial amount, despite the husband's claims of financial hardship.
title: Maintenance to wife, kids will get priority over claim of creditors: SC

description: India and Russia reaffirmed their strategic partnership, with Defence Minister Rajnath Singh emphasizing their strong bond during a meeting with President Putin.  Discussions focused on expediting S-400 deliveries, enhancing Sukhoi-30MKI maintenance, and expanding joint production of AK-203 rifles.  While Russia remains India's primary arms supplier, India is diversifying its procurement.
title: Rajnath meets Putin, affirms India will stand by Russia

description: Tesla's Optimus robot successfully navigated uneven, mulched terrain using neural networks, even while "blindfolded" without video input. Elon Musk and Milan Kovac shared videos demonstrating this progress, highlighting the robot's balance and adaptation abilities.
title: Musk shares video of Tesla's Optimus Robot achieving another 'feat'. Watch

description: Israeli Ambassador Reuven Azar stated Israel can learn from India's soft power approach in conflict narratives. Azar highlighted India's support for Israel's core interests while acknowledging differences on UNRWA aid and UN resolutions. He suggested potential progress in hostage negotiations and emphasized Israel's goal to dismantle Hamas' military capabilities in Gaza.
title: 'Israel can learn from India the use of soft power to win war of narratives'

description: Defence minister Rajnath Singh met with Russian President Vladimir Putin and defense minister Andrey Belousov, reaffirming India's support for Russia and highlighting their strong defense ties.  Discussions focused on joint military production, expedited delivery of S-400 missile systems, and strengthening India's domestic defense industry through collaboration. Singh also paid respects at the Tomb of the Unknown Soldier in Moscow.
title: Rajnath meets Putin in Moscow, says India will continue to stand by Russia

description: Maharashtra's opposition INDIA bloc will challenge the recent assembly election results in the Supreme Court, alleging EVM manipulation. Following a meeting with Arvind Kejriwal and Abhishek Singhvi, NCP leader Prashant Jagtap announced the decision. This comes after over 20 losing opposition candidates questioned the EVMs' integrity, citing discrepancies between polled votes and declared results.
title: INDIA bloc to move SC over EVMs 'manipulation' in Maharashtra polls

description: CM Punk inadvertently revealed footage of the Wyatt Sicks and Final Testament rehearsing their upcoming WWE match on Instagram.  The stables are currently engaged in a feud, with recent events involving supernatural elements and the return of Paul Ellering.  Fans are speculating whether this leak was intentional to further fuel interest in the storyline.
title: Punk accidentally shares clip of prominent WWE stables practicing match

description: A major Microsoft 365 outage disrupted access to Outlook, OneDrive, and Teams for users globally, including India, where complaints peaked around 3:19 pm IST.  Microsoft confirmed the issue, suggesting desktop applications as a temporary workaround while investigating the root cause. This marks the second Microsoft 365 outage in two weeks, raising concerns about service reliability.
title: Microsoft 365 outage that hit Outlook and Teams users is now resolved
Trump taps Khalistani sympathiser to head civil liberties division in justice dept

description: A Bengaluru techie, Atul Subhash, tragically died by suicide, leaving a 24-page note accusing his wife and her family of driving him to the extreme step. He alleged they filed false cases and demanded Rs 3 crore, detailing a campaign of harassment and extortion. Subhash's brother supports these claims, stating the relentless pressure led to the suicide.
title: 'Rs 3 cr for settlement, 9 cases’: Bengaluru techie’s brother alleges harassment

description: India has sought extradition of 178 fugitives from various countries over the past five years, with 23 successfully extradited since January 2019.  Sixty-five requests, including those for individuals accused of terrorism, are pending with US authorities.  India has extradition treaties with 48 countries and arrangements with 12 others, and continues to pursue diplomatic efforts to bring fugitives to justice.
title: India made 178 extradition requests but secured only 23 in past 5 years: Govt

description: Weakened by US-led forces, ISIS remnants in Syria exploit instability, particularly in the eastern desert.  A potential Assad regime fall and US troop withdrawal risk empowering the group, despite its current weakened state.  Increased attacks and shadow governance indicate a potential resurgence, raising concerns for regional stability.
title: Can fall of Assad lead to revival of Islamic State in Syria?

description: Rahul and Priyanka Gandhi met with victims of the Sambhal violence a week after being barred from the area.  The Congress leaders condemned the BJP's alleged role in the clashes, which erupted following a court-ordered mosque survey.  The violence resulted in five deaths and numerous injuries, stemming from a dispute over the site's historical religious identity.
title: Rahul, Priyanka meet Sambhal victims in Delhi after being denied entry

description: Former cricketer Mohammad Kaif points out the pressure on Rohit Sharma to perform both as a batter and captain in the Border-Gavaskar Trophy. Rohit's recent batting slump and Jasprit Bumrah's injury scare add to his challenges. India lost the second Test i Adelaide by 10 wickets.
title: Double trouble for Rohit: 'Score runs, manage Bumrah workload'

description: The BJP has released a video of Delhi CM Arvind Kejriwal's renovated official residence, calling it a "museum of corruption."  They allege Rs 45 crore was spent on renovations, highlighting luxurious features.  AAP dismisses the claims as baseless propaganda, accusing the BJP of diverting attention from critical issues like education and healthcare.
title: 'Museum of corruption': Delhi BJP shares clip of CM house; AAP hits back

description: Former skipper Rashid Latif urges Pakistan to boycott the Champions Trophy.  This follows India's refusal of a hybrid model for the 2025 edition.  Pakistan had agreed to the hybrid model but demanded reciprocal treatment for Indian events.  The BCCI rejected this, citing no security threats in India.  The ICC is now facing a new deadlock over the tournament's future.
title: 'Pak should boycott CT before BCCI ...': Rashid Latif
Will it be Congress-mukt INDIA? Mamata Banerjee's leadership pitch divides opposition bloc

description: Microsoft and OpenAI's partnership faces growing pains as their business models diverge.  Microsoft's AI CEO, Suleyman, predicts AGI is five to ten years away, contradicting OpenAI CEO Altman's more optimistic two-year timeline. Suleyman emphasizes the need for significant hardware advancements before AGI becomes a reality.
title: Microsoft AI CEO Mustafa Suleyman on tension with ChatGPT maker OpenAI

description: Canadian Prime Minister Justin Trudeau has warned of retaliatory measures if US President-elect Donald Trump imposes new tariffs, citing the success of similar actions in 2018. Trump, who recently dined with Trudeau, reiterated his intention to implement a 25% tariff on Canadian and Mexican imports unless migration and fentanyl flows are addressed.
title: What 'Governor' Trudeau said on Trump tariff threat

description: Legendary West Indian fast bowler Andy Roberts has advised Virat Kohli to concentrate on Test cricket to rediscover his form.  Kohli, currently facing a challenging phase in his career, recently broke a 16-month century drought in Perth. Roberts emphasised the importance of red-ball cricket for Kohli's resurgence and the overall improvement of top batter's performance in the longer format.
title: Kohli should 'focus' on Tests: Andy Roberts

description: Congress leader Rahul Gandhi advised party MPs to disregard comments from lower-ranking INDIA bloc members and focus on joint protests.  He emphasized the Congress party's capability to handle issues within the alliance and highlighted the effectiveness of their Adani protests in unsettling the government.  Gandhi encouraged innovative protest strategies and reiterated the importance of raising public concerns in Parliament.
title: 'Don't react': Rahul to Cong MPs as INDIA bloc weighs leadership options

description: Syria's Assad regime has fallen, transferring power to rebel forces. This follows protests and regime changes in Sri Lanka and Bangladesh, raising questions about Iran's stability. The fall of Assad and Hezbollah's weakening severely impacts Iran's regional influence and economy. Internal dissent in Iran is growing, fueled by economic hardship and the regime's perceived vulnerability.
title: Sri Lanka, Bangladesh and now Syria: Could Iran be the next?

description: Taylor Swift concluded her record-breaking Eras Tour with a tribute to boyfriend Travis Kelce, who achieved a career milestone in the NFL.  Swift altered lyrics in "Karma," referencing Kelce's team, the Kansas City Chiefs.  The couple has supported each other at games and concerts throughout their relationship, sparking speculation about Kelce's future with the Chiefs and potential successors.
title: Taylor Swift leaves Travis Kelce loving message during final Eras show

description: Google's 2024 Year in Search report for India revealed Indians' diverse interests.  Trending searches ranged from sports like IPL and Olympics to entertainment like "Stree 2" and K-dramas.
title: IPL, T20 World Cup and 8 other things that Indians Googled most for in 2024

description: South Australia clinched a dramatic two-run victory over Tasmania in a Sheffield Shield thriller. Chasing 429, Tasmania needed four runs off the final ball but a run-out on the last delivery sealed a remarkable win for South Australia. The match witnessed a tense finish with Tasmania losing four wickets for just four runs in the final nine balls.
title: Watch: 4 Runs, 1 Ball, 1 Wicket! Sheffield Shield's 'hell of a game'

description: The Indian Coast Guard apprehended two Bangladeshi fishing trawlers with 78 fishermen aboard for illegally fishing in Indian waters.  The trawlers, Laila-2 and Meghna-5, were intercepted near the international maritime boundary line and escorted to Paradip for investigation. This action follows increased Coast Guard patrols and aerial surveillance since August, aimed at preventing illegal migration and safeguarding maritime security.
title: Coast Guard seizes 2 Bangladeshi trawlers with 78 fishermen

description: Taylor Swift concluded her record-breaking Eras Tour in Vancouver with a heartfelt tribute to boyfriend Travis Kelce.  She altered lyrics in "Karma" and incorporated his signature dance move, acknowledging their budding romance.  The tour, a monumental success, grossed $2.2 billion, marking a significant chapter in Swift's career and personal life.
title: 'Karma is the guy in the Chiefs': Taylor Swift's tribute to Travis Kelce

description: China announced visa restrictions on US personnel accused of interfering in Hong Kong's affairs. This retaliatory move follows US sanctions against Chinese officials linked to Hong Kong's national security law.  Beijing condemned US actions as interference, while Washington criticized the jailing of Hong Kong opposition figures.  This escalating tension reflects ongoing disputes over Hong Kong's legal landscape and autonomy.
title: China imposes visa restrictions on US personnel over 'interference'

description: The UGC announced major changes to the 2025 CUET-UG exam, including reducing subjects to 37, shifting to exclusively computer-based testing, and standardizing exam duration to 60 minutes.  Candidates can now choose subjects not studied in Class 12, but are limited to five choices. These revisions aim to streamline the process and address past logistical challenges.
title: UGC announces major changes in CUET-UG 2025: Check key updates
7 dead, several injured in Hathras road accident

description: Following a crushing defeat in the pink-ball Test, India's cricket team, led by Rohit Sharma and Virat Kohli, engaged in rigorous red-ball practice in Adelaide. Their training focused on bolstering defensive techniques and shot selection ahead of the crucial third Test in Brisbane. Kohli, despite a recent century, worked on his form after two edged dismissals.
title: Watch: Virat Kohli rolls his arm over in net session

description: The Election Commission of India (ECI) announced that a mandatory count of Voter-Verified Paper Audit Trail (VVPAT) slips from the Maharashtra assembly elections revealed no discrepancies with the electronic voting machine (EVM) results.  This follows opposition parties' boycott of the assembly's special session, citing concerns about EVM integrity and alleged discrepancies between polled votes and declared results.
title: No mismatch in VVPAT slips, votes polled in Maharashtra polls: EC

description: Union Minister Kiren Rijiju dismissed the opposition's no-confidence motion against Rajya Sabha Chairman Jagdeep Dhankhar, citing the NDA's majority and Dhankhar's commitment to public welfare.  Rijiju condemned the motion, filed by 60 INDIA bloc MPs, who accuse Dhankhar of partisan conduct.  The motion is unlikely to succeed due to the opposition's lack of numbers in the Rajya Sabha.
title: 'NDA has majority': Rijiju on oppn's no-confidence motion against Dhankhar

description: Israeli Prime Minister Benjamin Netanyahu testified in his corruption trial, facing charges of bribery, fraud, and breach of trust. He denies wrongdoing, claiming political motivation, while managing the ongoing Gaza war and facing an ICC arrest warrant for alleged war crimes.
title: 'Great absurdity in charges': Netanyahu takes stand in corruption trial

description: Allahabad High Court Justice Shekhar Kumar Yadav's endorsement of the Uniform Civil Code (UCC) at a Vishva Hindu Parishad event sparked controversy and a Supreme Court intervention.  Critics, including Prashant Bhushan and Asaduddin Owaisi, questioned the judge's attendance and remarks, raising concerns about impartiality.  The Supreme Court has requested a detailed report from the Allahabad High Court regarding the incident.
title: Who is Shekhar Kumar Yadav, judge whose UCC remark triggered uproar

description: The University of Pennsylvania (UPenn) has shaped the lives of notable alumni like Donald Trump, Elon Musk, and Luigi Mangione, whose paths diverged significantly. Trump, Wharton Class of 1968, focused on real estate and finance, paving the way for his business and political career. Musk, graduating in 1997 with degrees in Economics and Physics, applied his interdisciplinary expertise to revolutionize technology. Mangione, an engineering graduate (2020), initially excelled in computer science and innovation but shocked the world with his recent arrest for the murder of UnitedHealthcare CEO Brian Thompson. His actions highlight a tragic turn from promise to notoriety.
title: What does Trump, Musk and UnitedHealthcare CEO murderer have in common?

description: The incoming Trump administration will meet with tech giants like Google, Meta, and TikTok.  They will discuss strategies to combat online drug sales.  Fentanyl is a key concern.  The meeting will explore current policies and challenges.  Trump's focus remains on the fentanyl crisis.  He plans tariffs and awareness campaigns.  Tech companies face scrutiny over their role in online drug sales.
title: Donald Trump's transition team invites Google, Meta, other tech giants to combat drug sales

description: Virat Kohli is diligently honing his back-foot technique in preparation for the extra bounce expected at the Gabba pitch in Brisbane, venue of the third Test against Australia. Harbhajan Singh observed Kohli's extensive net practice, focusing on playing off the back foot, recognizing its importance for success on the bouncy Brisbane track.
title: Virat working on 'Gabba-specific' plans to punch Aus back

description: Kansas City teenagers, supported by Travis Kelce's foundation, restored a 1969 Chevrolet Chevelle, converting it into an electric vehicle.  This three-year project, involving extensive metalwork and rebuilding, empowered the youth, teaching valuable skills and fostering hope.  The restored Chevelle is now being raffled off, symbolizing the transformative power of hard work and community collaboration.
title: Kelce helps teens turn abandoned Chevelle into life-changing project

description: Royal Challengers Bengaluru (RCB) revealed their rationale for releasing Faf du Plessis, citing fan input favoring him as an opener and a desire for a more explosive foreign opener. Dinesh Karthik emphasized the need for a batter with a high strike rate against spin, highlighting Phil Salt's impressive boundary percentage and run-scoring ability as key factors in their decision.
title: RCB explains their decision to opt for Phil Salt instead of Du Plessis

description: President-elect Donald Trump’s nomination of Harmeet K. Dhillon as Assistant Attorney General for Civil Rights has sparked controversy, particularly in New Delhi. Dhillon, a prominent Republican of Indian descent, has faced criticism for past social media posts allegedly supporting pro-Khalistani views, including unverified claims of India operating "death squads" targeting Sikh diaspora critics. Her remarks sharply contrast Trump’s efforts to strengthen ties with India and court Indian-American voters. While Trump has elevated several Indian-Americans to prominent roles, Dhillon’s nomination may alienate sections of the Indian-American community, whose support for Trump grew modestly in the 2024 election, particularly among men.
title: Is Trump's latest pick pro-Khalistan?

description: Mohammed Siraj, fined by the ICC for his send-off to Travis Head during the Adelaide Test, responded with a brief 'it's all good' when questioned.  He then excused himself to head to the gym.  Both Siraj and Bumrah skipped Tuesday's practice.  The incident stemmed from Siraj's dismissal of Head, with conflicting accounts of their post-wicket exchange later resolved.
title: 'I am going to ...': Siraj reacts on ICC fine

description: The Indian cricket team held a training session in Adelaide before the third Test against Australia in Brisbane.  Most batters practiced in the nets, while bowlers Bumrah and Siraj were rested. Meanwhile, Brisbane's weather forecast for the first day of the Test is not thretening, showing partly cloudy skies and maxium temperature in early 30s.
title: What Team India did in Adelaide today, travel plans, Brisbane weather

description: Walmart faced online criticism for selling underwear and slippers featuring Lord Ganesha, a revered Hindu deity.  The Hindu American Foundation called out the retailer for the disrespectful use of religious imagery.  Following the backlash, Walmart removed some of the Ganesha-printed products from its website, prompting appreciation from the Hindu community and others online.
title: Walmart featuring Lord Ganesha on underwear...: Outrage over print & more

description: NASA's Perseverance rover has unearthed a compelling clue in the hunt for past Martian life. A rock sample dubbed "Cheyava Falls," found in Jezero Crater, contains signs of ancient water and organic compounds. These building blocks of life, detected alongside potential energy sources, hint at an environment that may have once supported microbial life.
title: Nasa's new findings on Mars reveal critical evidence about planet

description: Former Australian pacer Damien Fleming has raised concerns over Jasprit Bumrah's fitness after the second Test against Australia.  Fleming questioned Bumrah bowling a particular over despite apparent discomfort, suggesting it revealed tactical secrets.  Bumrah's reduced pace and absence from training fueled speculation, though captain Rohit Sharma attributed it to workload management.
title: Is Bumrah fully fit? Fleming raises alarm, says 'no way that's cramp'

description: A 20-year-old woman, Afreen Shah, died in a BEST bus crash in Kurla, Mumbai, after her first day at a new job. Her father, Abdul Salim Shah, last spoke with her when she was looking for a ride home. The crash killed seven and injured 42.
title: Kurla bus accident: 20-year-old left for 1st day at new job, never to return

description: SC has sought report from the Allahabad high court concerning a speech delivered by Justice Shekhar Kumar Yadav at a VHP event.  Justice Yadav endorsed the Uniform Civil Code, emphasising its potential to foster social harmony and equality.  This follows previous controversial statements by the judge.
title: SC seeks report from Allahabad HC over Justice Yadav’s remarks at VHP event

description: Delhi chief minister Arvind Kejriwal announced a life insurance scheme of ₹10 lakh for auto drivers, along with other benefits like accident insurance, marriage assistance for daughters, uniform allowance, and coaching for children. This comes as part of AAP's campaign for the upcoming Delhi Assembly elections, aiming for a third term.
title: Delhi polls: Kejriwal announces Rs 10 lakh insurance for auto drivers

description: Jey Uso remains medically unfit following a brutal attack by Drew McIntyre.  McIntyre, returning after Bad Blood, explained his assault on Jey and Sami Zayn, citing their allegiance to Roman Reigns. He will face Zayn at WWE Saturday Night’s Main Event on December 14th.
title: WWE gives devastating update on Uso’s injury after McIntyre's attack

description: AAP is pursuing a three-pronged strategy for the Delhi assembly polls, emphasizing its subsidy schemes, criticizing the BJP-led central government, and replacing sitting MLAs to combat anti-incumbency.  The party is highlighting the benefits of its social welfare programs and attacking the BJP's record on law and order to secure a third consecutive victory.
title: Freebies, attack on Centre, new faces: How AAP plans to win Delhi, again

description: Health scientist Ollie Whitby highlights the importance of prioritizing well-being in our busy lives. Practical tips for a healthier 2025 include optimizing sunlight exposure, delaying caffeine, prioritizing morning cardio, and mindful hydration. Focus on whole foods, manage stress, prioritize sleep, and limit EMF exposure. Boost brain health with engaging activities, practice intermittent fasting, and maintain good posture.
title: 25 cheat codes for 2025 to completely transform your health

description: India contemplated changes for the crucial Brisbane Test. Cheteshwar Pujara recommended bringing in Washington Sundar for Ravichandran Ashwin. He advocated for keeping faith in pacer Harshit Rana. Rana had a tough outing in Adelaide. Sundar's all-round abilities made him a strong contender. The series was level at 1-1. India needed a win to boost their World Test Championship chances.
title: BGT: Pujara suggests key changes for India's playing XI

description: Singer Diljit Dosanjh paid tribute to poet Rahat Indori during his Indore concert by reciting his famous lines "Kisi ke baap ka Hindustan thode hi hai." This followed Bajrang Dal's protest against the concert, citing concerns over liquor, meat, and cultural impact.
title: Diljit Dosanjh dedicates Indore concert to Rahat Indori amid Bajrang Dal protests

description: YesMadam, a Noida-based salon home service startup, clarified that recent social media posts about firing stressed employees were part of a campaign to raise awareness about workplace stress.  They apologized for any distress caused and introduced a "Happy 2 Heal" program and India's first "De-Stress Leave" policy, offering six paid leaves and a complimentary spa session annually to each employee.
title: Poonam Pandey stunt? Startup that fired 100 employees after...
